Male.description: The back on Red-belled Woodpeckers is barred black and white unlike the solid black back on Red-headed Woodpecker. They also have a white face not red like the Red-headed Woodpecker.

Male (Northern).description: The back on Golden-fronted Woodpeckers is barred black and white unlike the solid black back on Red-headed Woodpecker.

Male.description: Pileated Woodpeckers are larger than Red-headed Woodpeckers with a red crest and dark back. They also lack the white wing patches seen on the folded wings of Red-headed Woodpeckers.
